milestone.title: 1.0.0 L1 process
milestone.description: A fully fleshed out pipeline, though it might not have all the corrections planned, that does all the basic steps of the L1 calibration.

comment.body: There was a small bug effecting the metadata for the flat interpolation, but the interpolation is fundamentally correct in my testing. Differences between flat interpolated and non-flat interpolated data comes from blending in a bad flat into data that used only a different flat originally. Better quality control for flat and dark images is required to fix this issue.

issue.title: Relax verification requirements for a processed day
issue.body:
Currently, a single file missing from the level 0 files causes a warning to be produced that must be checked manually.

Relax this requirement to allow `verification/max_missing` number of files to be missing in Boulder if they are also missing at MLSO servers.

- [x] add `verification/max_missing` option specification
- [x] check missing files via `ssh` to MLSO to see if they are missing there as well (files that are present at MLSO are actually a failure)
- [x] allow `verification/max_missing` missing files
